description.narrative: UNICEF Child Protection interventions led to improved Government and Civil Society Organizations capacity at national and sub-national level to enhance access to safe, quality, coordinated and comprehensive child protection services through the integrated case management and child-friendly justice, resulting in a total of 75,320 children (31,895 boys and 43,425 girls) receiving mainstream and emergency-focused Child Protection services, an increase from 54,382 children in 2018. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:13/01/2020
